time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates through the characters of both strings simultaneously using a for loop. If the characters at the same index are different, it increments the steps variable. Since there is only one character comparison per iteration, the time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the strings. The space complexity is O(1) because only a constant amount of memory is used, regardless of the length of the strings. The energy implications are low because the algorithm does not involve any complex operations or data structures.

